// A negative *integer* exponent that arrives as a rational (e.g. the
// result of `1 / -1`) used to call `Int::pow` with a negative right-hand
// side, which panicked unconditionally ("right hand side must not be
// negative") and aborted the whole process. It now computes the
// reciprocal, exactly like a plain negative integer exponent.
// expect-output: 1/2
print(2 ^ (1/-1));
